<$fill $name="body">

!! Plugin files

|!File |!Role |
|`controlpanel.tid` |Main hub UI — tagged `$:/tags/ControlPanel/SettingsTab`, renders sidebar + content layout |
|`default-panel.tid` |Fallback panel shown when a plugin has no `settings` tiddler; links to doc/overview or legacy doc-overview |
|`settings.tid` |core-hook's own settings entry (displays "no configurable settings" info card) |
|`documentation.tid` |Documentation tab — transcludes doc/overview if doc-template is installed, otherwise fallback |
|`readme.tid` |Plugin readme |
|`changelog.tid` |Version history table |
|`icon.tid` |SVG icon |
|`plugin.info` |Plugin metadata |
|`LICENSE.md` + `.meta` |MIT license (sidecar maps to `$:/plugins/rimir/core-hook/license`) |
|`README.md` |GitHub-facing readme |
|`test/test-hub.tid` |Regression test — verifies sidebar renders plugin names and content area |
|`doc/*.tid` |Doc-template documentation tiddlers (overview, architecture, dev-workflow, examples, faq, reference, tw-internals) |

!! Restart rules

|!Change |!Restart needed? |
|Any `.tid` file |Yes — all files are plugin shadow tiddlers, require server restart to update |

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">
core-hook is 100% wikitext — no JS modules. However, since all files are shadow tiddlers inside the plugin, a server restart is needed to pick up changes. Config changes via the browser UI take effect immediately.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! Adding a plugin to the hub

To make your plugin appear in the settings hub:

# Create a tiddler `$:/plugins/rimir/<slug>/settings` inside your plugin directory
# Add `"settings"` to the `list` field in `plugin.info`
# Restart the server — the hub discovers the plugin automatically via the `$:/plugins/rimir/` prefix filter

!! Dependencies

* ''theme'' — CSS classes for the hub layout (`rr-settings-hub`, `rr-settings-sidebar`, `rr-settings-content`, etc.)

</$fill>
</$transclude>
